Hangman Game in Python
Project Overview

This project is a simple text-based Hangman Game developed in Python. The game randomly selects a word from a predefined list, and the player must guess the word one letter at a time. The player has a limited number of incorrect attempts (6 tries) to identify the hidden word before the game ends.

Features
Random word selection using the random module.
Interactive command-line gameplay.
Tracks guessed letters to avoid duplicate guesses.
Displays remaining attempts after each guess.
Reveals correctly guessed letters in their positions.
Win and lose conditions with appropriate messages.
Technologies Used
Python 3
Random Module
Loops (while, for)
Conditional Statements (if, elif, else)
Lists and Strings
How It Works
A random word is selected from a predefined list.
The word is hidden using underscores (_).
The player enters one letter at a time.
If the letter exists in the word, it is revealed.
If the letter is incorrect, the number of remaining tries decreases.
The game continues until:
The player guesses the entire word, or
The player runs out of attempts.
How to Run
Install Python 3 on your system.
Save the code in a file named hangman.py.
Open a terminal or command prompt.
Run the following command:
python hangman.py
